  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0db3\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0d8b\u0dab \u0db8\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca?",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A monkey flu death from India?",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is reported that a young man who showed symptoms of 'monkey fever' (monkey pox) has died from the Indian state of Kerala.",
        "Kerala health authorities have started an investigation into the death of the young man, and if the young man is confirmed to be infected with 'monkey pox', this will be the first 'monkey fever' death to be reported from India.",
        "Immediately after the youth's death, Kerala State Health Minister Veena George ordered an immediate inquiry into the death. Accordingly, tissue samples of the deceased youth were sent for testing.",
        "The health department has explained that this young man came to Kerala from abroad, and if he was infected with 'monkey fever', it must have happened while he was coming from abroad.",
        "So far, four people infected with 'monkey fever' have been found in India and it is also said that the first person infected with monkey fever has fully recovered.",
        "Monkey fever is not a deadly virus. It is fatal to immunocompromised people. This is because of the complications caused by the virus.",
        "'Monkey fever' or 'monkey pox' is a very fast-spreading virus confined to Africa. This is a cross between chicken pox and small pox, and vaccines developed for small pox can suppress 'monkey fever'.",
        "The 'monkey flu' virus has now spread to 78 countries causing a global emergency and more than 18,000 infected people have been reported. The cities of California and New York in America have also declared states of emergency due to 'monkey fever'.",
        "Apart from Africa, 'monkey flu' deaths are also being reported from Spain and Brazil. That is, two deaths from Spain and one death from Brazil."
      ],
